But in the face of this, man only makes one ademanent.
“Everyone says a thing,” he says with a bad face.
Ostrava is becoming a great test laboratory for liberalization.
After New Year’s Eve, the vast majority of flats in the Czech Republic have so far been rented under a regulated rent.
That is why Aktuáln<0xC4><0x9B>.cz decided to visit the "laboratory" in person.
The RPG mining waiting room is one of four in Ostrava and, on Tuesday at nine, it was already full.
Right next to the doors are the security guards and next to them a machine to pick up number.
"Rent 2011", can be read on a light button of your touch screen.
