How to choose the mattress and the boxer: women and men look for different things
Nothing of a pompous frame for the bed; what really gives its quality to a good bed is the surface for lying down, i.e. the mattress and the boxer.
First of all, they must be complemented perfectly so that they adapt to the specific users.
During the election numerous elements come into play, including the weight, height, health status and sex of the owner.
Also important is the type of interior in which the mattress and box box is located.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend cabin that doesn’t usually have heating, latex mattresses should not be used because they “heat” more slowly.
In addition, they tend to weigh considerably more than the usual polyurethane mattresses.
Therefore, it is necessary to turn them around more frequently.
If the channels of the center are not properly aerated and, above, they are on a firm base, they keep the moisture inside.
When choosing a bed, customs also influence.
Anyone who has spent a lot of time abroad often uses a very high mattress with a soft coat and will have trouble feeling good on a lower, hard surface.
“Almost all of the hockey players who came back from the NHL complained that they didn’t sleep as well here.”
"For their crushed shoulders, heels and hips they needed mattresses with a soft layer of viscoelastic."
"These types of mattresses are also recommended for people with diabetes who have problems with the nervous system, so they misreceive information from the joints and the skin," explains Sylva Hadamcziková, who specializes in quilted furniture.
Many hockey players, like other customers, have long preferred viscoelastic mattresses.
"Today there is no problem anymore, because they have these suitable Tempur and the Italian Magniflex, but also the Czech brand Tropico."
You no longer have to be an NHL player to appreciate the viscoelastic.
This "miracle" works in a very simple way.
Optimizes your stiffness and shape depending on the heat absorbed or adapts to your body heat.
Nothing exerts pressure; during the night, it will not turn like after a hard match.
He just sleeps better.
The viscoelastic also works as a protection against sores.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add to your height the length of your feet, that is, between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for a person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, in total 180 cm.
In the case of single rooms, e.g. singles, a minimum of between 120 and 140 cm is recommended.
So that a possible visit is also comfortable.
"If not, you can apply a simple rule to calculate the width: when lying on your face, you should have your hands comfortably shrugged towards your elbows," advises the engineer Helena Prokopová, an expert from Cechu <0xC4><0x8D>alouník<0xC5><0xAF> a dekoratér<0xC5><0xAF>, who has been working for many years on the issue of healthy sleep and the ergonomics of furniture.
In double rooms, each needs their own boxer and mattress, so during the purchase you have to pay attention to combine the height of the mattresses.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to mount the beds at different heights, which is not always possible in all beds.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, models with springs interior a minimum of 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters are for the layer that adapts to the shapes and smoothes.
"By touching it with your hand or sitting on the mattress, you should certainly not notice the docks," warns Helena Prokopová.
Each mattress requires a certain type of box box.
The fully padded bedrooms, in which the mattress and base are like Siamese, make no sense in the bedroom.
Mattresses breathe poorly and cannot wash their cover, which today is often done.
And, since every night we sweat between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat, it is clear that after about five or seven years the mattress will begin to remind us of a large (and congested) sieve.
For this reason, specialists reject slogans that speak of a mattress life of up to 25 years or even a lifetime warranty.
However, everything has an but.
For this reason, vendors give a tip: on mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, carefully take care of cleaning and washing the cover, but better add a mattress protector that can be easily removed and washed.
Although zippered mattress covers are currently manufactured throughout their perimeter, so when they are opened they are left in two parts (something very important for washing and the size of the washing machine!), their handling on larger models (and by a single person) when lifting the mattress can seem like a fight between a fly weight and a heavy weight.
In bed, instead of a boxer, do you have a firm board?
Never! Never!
As much for the beds designed for one night visits.
However, you should make (if you do not already have them) ventilation holes in the board and should be used with a mattress with springs inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with the springs in bags (such as the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattresses should not be used on such bases.
For sheet beds containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses (e.g., a combination of latex and coconut fiber) may be used, although a bed bed with a greater number of sheets, 28 or more, in which the sheets of the lumbar zone are stiffened and can be regulated, is always better.
Articulated sheet beds should not be used with a spring mattress, as it does not react to reclining.
In addition to adjusting the rigidity of the sheets, shoulder protection can also be used.
This is a special fixation of the sheets that allows you to press or even tilt the sheets in such a way that they "rode" perfectly to the shoulders during sleep.
For men who have very wide shoulders, this is very important.
They are even remembered by mattress makers who, in the "males", began to use a softer area precisely around the shoulders.
They also remember women, for whom they put a softer area around the hips.
For the most demanding customers, there are beds with cross structure or boards with so-called multi-twist damping.
The pressure is distributed between different points and the tension is reduced.
You should also keep in mind that even if you use the right mattress and boxer, if you use a bad pillow (large and "mully"), most of the advantages will disappear.
The basic rule is simple: the pillow must hold the head and the corners can only reach the shoulders, so that the muscles of the same can be relaxed.
The recommended suitable size is 50 x 60 cm, something normal for example in Scandinavia.
When lying on your side, the pillow should be at the same level (when combined with the shoulder reinforcement boxer or the softer area of the mattress) as the height of the shoulders.
Modern mattresses seem to have something to do with the original straw-filled mattresses.
Manufacturers continue to use more and more natural materials or, at least, mixtures.
In fact, biological mattresses are fashionable.
The petroleum-based raw materials, with which the polyurethane foam is made, are filled with natural oils, for example castor or soybean.
In fact, virtually all known manufacturers use soybeans.
"Biological, in the case of mattresses, means that the center is made only of materials of natural origin," explains Petr Va<0xC5><0xA1>í<0xC4><0x8D>ek of the company Tropico Plus.
Also, natural substances are used during the manufacture of the mattress cover, one of the first aloe vera.
But you can also opt for microcapsules, which release a fresh aroma to forest or lavender.
There are also differences for men and women.
While men are "cooled" with vegetable extracts from the breeze, so that the mattress cover absorbs heat and cools the body, women prefer to "warm" the cover.
Red pepper extract improves blood circulation, so women feel warmer.
Favorites currently?
Mattresses made of cold foam, which are more porous, with an adapted cell structure, which makes them more permeable than those of normal polyurethane and offer more permeability.
The combination of various stiffnesses of cold foam and viscoelastic allow to manufacture mattresses of various zones that know perfectly where the head, shoulders and heels go.
A good quality mattress will cost you from seven thousand crowns upwards.
Those who perform a therapeutic function usually have a lower VAT rate, since they are considered as health facilities.
The first to gain this advantage in the Czech Republic was Gumotex.
It is difficult to save on mattresses and beds.
Sometimes you can approve offers from manufacturers or sellers, who sometimes offer two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, the Magniflex brand offers Duofreeze mattresses with memory foam attached to the cover for 11,990 crowns.
The second one is free of charge.
The era of viscoelastic with an open cell structure and high density began with Tempur's "cosmic" material.
Initially it emerged as a material for NASA, because during takeoffs astronauts were subjected to a huge overload.
Tempur softens with heat and hardens with cold.
Consequently, the warm human body exerts a perfect effect and optimally adapts its pressure.
Therefore, it is ideal to prevent sores from occurring, but also to improve comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foam is used not only in mattresses, but also for sanitary products, for example for pillows that are placed under the legs and relieve them, as well as their circulation.
Domestic manufacturers, for example, use Eucatherm C or Twinsaver foam and the like.
