The company will take to court those who disagree with the new rental.
Regulated rentals, which benefit residents of around 300,000 floors, could increase next year to 10 percent.
The young Czechs get drunk with Fernet and rum. The beer is no longer in mode, because it works slowly
Fernet, rum, vodka and even good whiskeys stolen from his parents.
These are the drinks that cause young drinkers under the age of fifteen to end up in medical care.
Children who end up lying in the hospital continuously to overcome the hangover are no longer an exception.
This is derived from the experience of doctors who encounter such cases in hospital pediatric admissions.
“Drinking beer or wine is no longer in fashion, because it takes a long time to get drunk.”
“Now the fashion is strong alcoholic beverages,” Lud<0xC4><0x9B>k Pelikán, head of pediatrics at Ho<0xC5><0x99>ovice Hospital in central Bohemia, told Právo.
"When they manage to get a bottle from their father's cupboard, it can be whiskey, but it's usually Fernet and vodka."
“Vodka has the advantage that it lightens with juice and doesn’t smell that much,” he explains.
This is also confirmed by the spokeswoman of Motol University Hospital, Eva Jurinová.
"Normally it's Fernet or rum."
"These are modern alcoholic beverages, particularly among schoolchildren."
“In some cases, they use spirits they picked up at home,” Jurinová adds.
According to Chief Pelikán, thirteen- and fourteen-year-old drinkers usually appear in hospitals.
Before Ho<0xC5><0x99>ovice, where he has worked since this year, he worked for a decade in pediatrics in Motol, where ambulances took young people from nearby areas.
"A girl had to come in maybe four times."
"It started at the age of twelve, when she was brought in with 3.5 alcohol in her blood, plus a mixture with ecstasy," the department's doctor said of the case.
"He was at the Hole<0xC5><0xA1>ovice Fair at some dance party."
"The interesting thing is that his mother wasn't even surprised that his daughter disappeared for 48 hours," he said.
It is precisely the lack of interest of parents or even their clear tolerance for drinking by their children that is considered the main cause of the increase in alcohol consumption among young people.
Experts point out that, in the case of children, one cannot speak properly of dependence.
"An alcoholic is a person who has had a chronic dependence on alcohol for several years, with all the phenomena associated with it, which does not occur in children."
"In those who drink alcohol repeatedly, it is rather due to a systematically failed social or family environment," explains Chief Pelikán.
According to spokeswoman Jurinová, 40 drunk children were hospitalized in Motol’s pediatric clinic until mid-November this year.
However, the statistics only show those who come with severe poisoning and should remain in the hospital.
The young drinkers who, after the ambulant medical examination, go home with the parents or with the police, do not count.
In addition to the cases where children simply gather after school and drink spirits, for Pelikán there are three seasonal ups and downs to mention: the day of witches, the end of the year and the end of the school year.
"In such a circumstance, they drink for bad grades or, on the contrary, they celebrate the beginning of the holiday."
“On Witch Day I’ve come to see up to seven drunken children on admissions at once,” Pelikán adds.
Drinkers who spend the night in detox under the supervision of doctors, paradoxically, have the advantage that the next day they do not suffer a terrible hangover at home.
Morning headache, caused by dehydration and lack of glucose, is avoided by injecting a serum with glucose and the nutrients that the body lacks.
"They get it much better, because after the hectic night, they get up well and do not hurt anything."
“They are only confused about where they are,” Pelikán says, adding that patients often lose their mood at least when they see the expenses they have generated.
The ambulance transfer and hospitalization in a room for serious patients cost tens of thousands of crowns.
“I have often used cost as a means of educating them, when on the visit I tell the children directly how much their drunkenness has cost and that they would have to spend the whole summer on a youth job so that you would earn enough to pay yourself that night,” Pelikán adds.
Health insurance, in his opinion, perhaps as a regressive measure, which usually reimburses people for treatment expenses, does not do so in the case of children who drink.
Two L-159 aircraft are in foreign hands for the first time in Spain
Two L-159 aircraft of a total of five, for which the Czech Ministry of Defense replaced the Casa C-295M aircraft, departed on Tuesday for Seville, where the manufacturer of the aircraft Casa - EADS is located.
This is the first time such a device has been in the hands of anyone other than the Czech army.
