Li Xuedong, 40, a coordinator assigned to the male squadron, remained behind, with his white badge turned over to hide his name.
As female officers, coordinators, men aged 40 and over, play a purely supportive role.
Unlike them, they are not taught how to maintain an elegant image.
“Sometimes we fight verbally.”
“Sometimes we fight physically,” Mr. Li said naturally.
