"Pakistan has had to hire staff with strict religious beliefs to protect nuclear facilities; given falling educational and cultural levels, extremist organizations have more opportunities to recruit people working on nuclear or missile programs," Yuri Korolev, a Russian foreign ministry expert, said at a meeting with his U.S. counterparts.
The latest in the documentation leaked by the Julian Assange portal is the ever-decreasing cooperation between the US and Pakistan on nuclear proliferation issues and Pakistan’s high rate of nuclear weapons production.
